# Test Scenarios
###############################################################################

### Scenario 1: Monitor under load
### Step 1: Get baseline metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/metrics

### Step 2: Trigger async operations (run multiple times)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/3
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/4
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/5

### Step 3: Check metrics again to see active threads
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/metrics

###

### Scenario 2: Compare with HikariCP metrics
### Get thread pool metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/metrics

### Get HikariCP metrics
GET http://localhost:8080/api/monitoring/hikari

###

### Scenario 3: Monitor queue behavior
### Step 1: Get initial state
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/status

### Step 2: Flood with async requests (run all at once)
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/async
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/async/1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/customers/async/2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/1
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/2
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/3
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/4
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/5
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/6
GET http://localhost:8080/api/products/v2/7

### Step 3: Check queue size immediately
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/status

###

### Scenario 4: View all details
GET http://localhost:8080/api/threadpool/details

